create a git repo
create code.py and code to it
before init the dvc add and comit the file in the git
install dvc and dvc init
when we init dvc we get .dvc and .dvcignore file
now make a dir s3 [Git stores small files (code).
DVC TRACKS large files, but stores the actual data in a different folder or remote storage (like S3).]
now we do "dvc remote add -d myremote s3"
now "dvc add data/"  [we will get error then follow the instructions]
now "git add .gitignore data.dvc"
now "dvc commit and then dvc push"
